{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":99466,"duration_api_ms":97598,"num_turns":22,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f209bafd-22f3-459c-a7ba-a6ac3d89041c","total_cost_usd":1.03436475,"usage":{"input_tokens":16,"cache_creation_input_tokens":67589,"cache_read_input_tokens":1014107,"output_tokens":4192,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":67589,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":16,"outputTokens":4192,"cacheReadInputTokens":1014107,"cacheCreationInputTokens":67589,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.03436475,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 91 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored)","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","Amendment fr-11-9348c590 FIXED: fs.rs:2449-2460 now emits tracing::warn! with bead_id, timestamp, existing_details, and requested_details before replacing malformed legacy completion details (starts_with 'project=' but unparseable). Operators can now audit when this lossy fallback fires.","Amendment fr-11-3f2dfcd6 FIXED: find_matching_running_task_run (model.rs:437-442) now checks matching_running_entries.as_slice() as a whole — the pattern `[entry] if entry.run_id.is_none()` only matches when the runless entry is the SOLE open attempt. With mixed state [(run_id=None, Running), (run_id='run-2', Running)], the two-element slice falls to `_ => None`, and the caller at fs.rs:2837 rejects via the `matching_running_entries.len() > 1` ambiguity guard.","Amendment fr-11-3f2dfcd6 model test verified: find_matching_running_task_run_rejects_mixed_legacy_and_named_open_attempts (model.rs:859-892) seeds (run_id=None, Running) + (run_id='run-2', Running) and asserts find_matching_running_task_run returns None for run_id='run-3'.","Amendment fr-11-3f2dfcd6 integration test verified: start_rejects_mixed_legacy_and_named_open_attempts (service.rs:2794-2860) performs the same scenario end-to-end and asserts 'ambiguous' error.","Amendment fr-11-84b6b1d6 FIXED in start path: backfill_running_entry (fs.rs:2693-2714) now pattern-matches on entry.plan_hash.as_deref() — when the existing hash differs from the requested hash, it returns Err with plan_hash_conflict_details instead of silently ignoring.","Amendment fr-11-84b6b1d6 FIXED in completion path: update_task_run (fs.rs:3086-3102) non-terminal branch now pattern-matches entry.plan_hash.as_deref() — conflicting plan_hash returns AppError::CorruptRecord with plan_hash_conflict_details instead of silently preserving the stale value.","Amendment fr-11-84b6b1d6 FIXED in terminal replay path: incompatible_terminal_update check (fs.rs:3058-3064) includes Self::option_conflicts(entry.plan_hash.as_deref(), plan_hash) so terminal replays with conflicting plan_hash are also rejected.","Amendment fr-11-84b6b1d6 start test verified: start_retry_rejects_conflicting_plan_hash (service.rs:2730-2791) starts with plan-v1, retries with plan-v2, asserts 'conflicting plan_hash' error; lineage retains plan-v1 and remains Running.","Amendment fr-11-84b6b1d6 completion test verified: completion_rejects_conflicting_plan_hash (service.rs:1716-1800) starts with plan-v1, completes with plan-v2, asserts 'conflicting plan_hash' error; snapshot remains Active with bead-1 active, lineage retains plan-v1 and remains Running.","All prior acceptance criteria remain satisfied: milestone state answers 'what happened to bead X?', controller can update linkage after each run outcome, all new fields are optional for backward compatibility with existing NDJSON data"],"findings_or_gaps":["All three final-review amendments (fr-11-9348c590, fr-11-3f2dfcd6, fr-11-84b6b1d6) have been addressed with code changes and regression tests in completion round 12.","AppError::RunStartFailed is still used (service.rs ~line 555 and backfill_running_entry at fs.rs:2696) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes and plan_hash conflicts in update_task_run and start paths. A more specific error variant would be semantically cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue — carried forward from prior reviews.","The outstanding risk — milestone mutations span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction — remains. All paths are serialized by the milestone mutation lock and replay-safe, making this an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage.","The matching_running_task_runs helper (fs.rs:2608-2621) used in record_task_run_start to check for ambiguous open attempts performs a full scan of all entries. For typical milestone sizes this is negligible, but worth noting."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"d8473f76-4a43-404a-bb63-20fe1f0d83da"}
